Title:  Steps for Adding a New Field

Tags:   fields

Body:

1. Add Standard labels (proper and common) to the NotenikConstants class.
2. Create a new xxxValue class in the values group.
3. Create a new xxxType class in the values group
4. If needed, create a new xxxPickList class in the values group. 
5. Add the new field to the AllTypes class in the values group
6. If this will be a commonly used field, add the new field to the CollectionPrefsViewController class in the collectionPrefs group
7. Add the field label to the FieldLabel class, if needed. 
8. Add the new field definition to the NoteCollection class
9. Add the appropriate field-specific methods to the Note class. 
10. Modify the NoteLineParser class if there is any special parsing logic for the new field type. 
11. Modify the NoteLineMaker class if there is any special logic for writing out a Note with this field. 
12. Modify the ApplyTemplateValues class if there is any special logic associated with setting Collection field definitions, etc. 
13. Add the xxxPickList class to the ValuePickLists class, in the values group (???)
14. Create a new xxxTokenDelegate class in the views group, for a Tokenized field
15. Create a new xxxView class in the views Group
16. Add new xxxView class to ViewFactory in the views group
17. Update NoteFieldsToHTML and/or NoteDisplay for any special display logic. 
18. Modify the saveTemplateFile method in the FileIO class if there is any special logic used when saving the field to the Collection template file. 

